sql:
SELECT models.model_name, algorithms.algorithm_name
FROM models
INNER JOIN algorithms ON models.algorithm_id = algorithms.algorithm_id;

external_knowledge:
'Recently developed' refers to models created in the last 30 days;
'Active users' are those with the 'is_active' flag set to 1;
'Data Science team members' belong to the 'Data Science' department.

- "surpassed the high bar of excellence" refers to models with a test score greater than 0.95;
- "continue to shine" means the models are active (is_active = 1);
- "guiding stars (algorithms)" refers to the algorithms associated with the models;
- "creative minds (users)" refers to the users who created the models.

sql:
SELECT models.model_name, algorithms.algorithm_name 
FROM models 
LEFT JOIN algorithms ON models.algorithm_id = algorithms.algorithm_id;
